goals.question: What is the distribution of regions across the United States?
goals.visualization: map of the United States with regions colored by income group
goals.rationale: This will help identify if there are any geographic patterns in the income distribution.

```python
import seaborn as sns
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = sns.barplot(x='group', y='pct', data=data, ci=None)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of income groups across all regions?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
```

```python
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    avg_pct = data.groupby('group')['pct'].mean().reset_index()
    chart = sns.lineplot(x='group', y='pct', data=avg_pct)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        chart.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("What is the average percentage of households in each income group?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

```python
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    highest_income_group = data[data['group'] == '200000+']
    sns.barplot(x='pct', y='region', data=highest_income_group, ci=None)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    max_pct = highest_income_group['pct'].max()
    plt.axvline(max_pct, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Max: {max_pct:.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    
    plt.title('Which region has the highest percentage of households in the highest income group?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

```python
    plt.title('What is the correlation between total number of households and percentage of households in the highest income group?', wrap=True)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

```python
import seaborn as sns
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import geopandas as gpd
from mpl_toolkits.axes_grid1 import make_axes_locatable

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    # Load US map shapefile
    us_map = gpd.read_file("https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PublicaMundi/MappingAPI/master/data/geojson/us-states.json")
    
    # Merge data with US map
    data_merged = us_map.set_index("name").join(data.set_index("name"))
    
    # Plot the map with regions colored by income group
    ax = data_merged.plot(column="group", cmap="coolwarm", legend=True, edgecolor="black", linewidth=0.5)
    
    # Set title
    plt.title("What is the distribution of regions across the United States?", wrap=True)
    
    # Set axis labels
    plt.xlabel("Longitude")
    plt.ylabel("Latitude")
    
    # Rotate x-axis labels if necessary
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.xticks(rotation=45)
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```
